    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I disagree with this. In general I don't think any contract that receives ether should be `selfdestruct`ed. That is because once the contract is destroyed all ether sent to it will be lost.\r\n\r\nIn the case of crowdsales, once the crowdsale is over it should reject all ether sent to it. If the contract is destroyed, however, there will be no code to reject these transactions.",
